+# Release v0.2.0 — Platform Migration
+
+_Released 2026-05-27 · Bump type: **MINOR** (0.1.0 → 0.2.0)_
+
+## Why this version
+
+The project is pre-1.0 (0.x). Under SemVer's 0.x rules — and per this repo's stated
+convention in `CHANGELOG.md` — **breaking changes increment the MINOR version** rather
+than MAJOR. This release is a breaking toolchain/platform upgrade, so `0.1.0 → 0.2.0`.
+(Post-1.0 the same changes would be a MAJOR bump.)
+
+## Headline
+
+Full front-end platform migration. No product features, routes, or screening behavior
+changed — this is tooling only. **Re-run `npm install` after pulling.**
+
+## Breaking changes (platform)
+
+- **Next.js 14 → 16** (App Router). Requires Node.js ≥ 20.
+- **React 18 → 19.** Components relying on React 18 behavior may need review.
+- **Tailwind CSS 3 → 4.** Styling now builds via `@tailwindcss/postcss`; PostCSS config
+  no longer lists `tailwindcss`/`autoprefixer` directly.
+- **TypeScript 5 → 6.** Strict `npm run typecheck` now runs against TS 6; JSX transform
+  switched to `react-jsx`.
+- **ESLint 9 → 10.** `@eslint/js`, `@next/eslint-plugin-next`, and the React Hooks plugin
+  moved to matching majors.
+
+## Dependencies
+
+- Google Generative AI SDK `0.21.0 → 0.24.1`.
+- Dev dependencies aligned to the toolchain above (`@types/*`, `globals`, `postcss`,
+  `typescript-eslint`).
+
+## Upgrade steps
+
+1. `git pull`
+2. `npm install` (the dependency tree changed substantially)
+3. `npm run typecheck && npm run build` to confirm a clean build
+
+## Provenance
+
+- Migration commit: `2fee916` "Upgrade Next.js dependencies".
+- Changelog entry: `CHANGELOG.md` → `[0.2.0]`.
+- Tag: annotated `v0.2.0`.
+

